This paper deals with the abstraction of linear dynamic networks and the selection of appropriate node signals for local module identification. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including systems and control (cs.SY), machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and signal processing (cs.SI). However, since the paper focuses on the dynamics of networks and the selection of input signals, we believe that cs.SY is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, and cs.SI.
